    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-24T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/478</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-24T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 137, September 13, 10 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d416fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_249">p. 249</ref>.</note> For
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>:</p>
                <p>Are the Allies unable to manage erecting shops as you state because 120 Baldwin
                    men sent home? Department has conferred with <persName corresp="#p_FSM1"
                        >Felton</persName> and both desire full statement of existing conditions at
                    Vladivostok and what you think should be done to meet situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
